abstract: Greg Pence, the vice president’s brother, is mounting something of a stealth campaign, years after leading a chain that went bankrupt and being sued over personal debts.
snippet: Greg Pence, the vice president’s brother, is mounting something of a stealth campaign, years after leading a chain that went bankrupt and being sued over personal debts.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBUS, Ind. — When you have the best known name in your congressional district and your younger brother is a heartbeat away from the presidency, it is difficult to run a stealth campaign. But Greg Pence is doing a pretty good job of it.

abstract: Under siege by the president’s allies in the House, Mr. Rosenstein has acceded to some demands. But his allies worry that may expose the Justice Department to political meddling.
snippet: Under siege by the president’s allies in the House, Mr. Rosenstein has acceded to some demands. But his allies worry that may expose the Justice Department to political meddling.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — He has a reputation as a principled lawyer. He has worked for both Republican and Democratic attorneys general. He has a jugular instinct in courtroom battles but a distaste for political ones.

abstract: Spring men’s wear that channels the photographer Robert Mapplethorpe’s visual world.
snippet: Spring men’s wear that channels the photographer Robert Mapplethorpe’s visual world.
lead_paragraph: Exploring topics such as black male sexuality and the underground BDSM scene, Robert Mapplethorpe immortalized the marginalized communities of early 1980s New York City with his striking images — and challenged conservative notions of beauty. While his subjects were just as often unclothed, leather wear appeared frequently in Mapplethorpe’s photographic world — for example, in his iconic X Portfolio — as a symbol of both sensuality and subversion. And that visual language is as relevant as ever in fashion today. Inspired by the late photographer’s work, we picked the standout leather pieces from the spring/summer 2018 men’s collections.

headline_main: This Season’s Leather Pieces, Inspired by ’80s New York

abstract: Lauren Ambrose stars as a newly empowered flower girl in a gorgeous revival that transforms the classic musical into an ur-text for the #MeToo moment.
snippet: Lauren Ambrose stars as a newly empowered flower girl in a gorgeous revival that transforms the classic musical into an ur-text for the #MeToo moment.
lead_paragraph: Poor Eliza. It’s not enough that her own father sells her for five pounds to the bully phonetician Henry Higgins. Or that Higgins strips her of her ragged clothes and Cockney accent so she can become a refined if useless lady.

headline_main: Review: Whose ‘Fair Lady’? This Time, Eliza’s in Charge

abstract: Judge Kimba M. Wood is weighing whether to appoint someone to help review materials seized from Michael D. Cohen, President Trump’s personal lawyer.
snippet: Judge Kimba M. Wood is weighing whether to appoint someone to help review materials seized from Michael D. Cohen, President Trump’s personal lawyer.
lead_paragraph: Federal prosecutors and lawyers for President Trump’s personal attorney, Michael D. Cohen, have each proposed to a judge the names of possible candidates to serve as a “special master” to assist in the review of materials seized last week by the F.B.I. from Mr. Cohen.

abstract: In 30 years on the bench, Judge Kimba Wood has handled several prominent matters. But the case of President Trump’s lawyer could be her most challenging.
snippet: In 30 years on the bench, Judge Kimba Wood has handled several prominent matters. But the case of President Trump’s lawyer could be her most challenging.
lead_paragraph: Judge Kimba M. Wood had barely finished a hearing this week that involved both Michael D. Cohen, President Trump’s lawyer, and — in a stunning revelation — the Fox News host Sean Hannity, when the right-wing media machine started going after her.
